<item>
            <title>[LU-9720] sanity test_42c: &apos;beforewrites 72 == afterwrites 72 on truncate</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9720</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/871bb8ea-5ce7-11e7-a74a-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/871bb8ea-5ce7-11e7-a74a-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_42c failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;beforewrites 72 == afterwrites 72 on truncate
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this fail is seen in the same test as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9656&quot; title=&quot;sanity: test_42a failed: &amp;#39;60 &amp;lt; 65&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9656&quot;&gt;LU-9656&lt;/a&gt; it occurs in a different subtest and the error looks quite different.&lt;br/&gt;
Raising it as a distinct ticket.&lt;br/&gt;
I will let an expert decide if it&apos;s a dup or not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity 42c&lt;/p&gt;</description>
